# waddle_display (`apps/waddle_display`)

- **SOLID**: ports under `lib/blob/`, `lib/secrets/`, `lib/data/`, `lib/api/`, `lib/window/`, etc.; composition in `lib/main.dart`. Repositories own Drift access; HTTP handlers delegate to repositories; no secrets in SQLite.
- **TDD**: tests first for new behavior; `test/` mirrors `lib/`. **`dart_test.yaml`** caps each test at **60s** so hangs fail fast; use `test(..., timeout: ...)` only when a test truly needs more wall time.
- **Coverage**: keep `apps/waddle_display/lib/` at **≥ 90%** line coverage when practical.
- **Dependencies**: justify new packages in PR/commit message.
- **No drive-by refactors** unrelated to the task.
- **Docs stay current**: if behavior, config/env vars, API surface, or operator workflow changes, update docs in the same change set (for example `apps/waddle_display/README.md`, `.env.example`, and runbooks), or state why docs are unchanged.
- **Drift migrations required**: any schema/data-shape change under `packages/waddle_shared/lib/persistence/` must include migration updates plus tests that validate upgrade/read compatibility.
- **Pre-commit checks**: before committing changes under `apps/waddle_display/`, run `flutter analyze` from that directory and ensure **zero** issues (warnings count). [`.github/workflows/ci.yml`](../../.github/workflows/ci.yml) runs the same command and fails the build on any issue. Test-file pitfalls that recur here (drift/`flutter_test` ambiguity, orphaned `final` fields, redundant `!` after promotion) are covered in [`waddle-view-tests.mdc`](waddle-view-tests.mdc); the [`run-waddle-checks`](../../.cursor/skills/run-waddle-checks/SKILL.md) skill bundles the full local CI mirror.
- **Kiosk fatal-vs-recoverable**: the kiosk restarts the process on every uncaught error via [`app_fatal_error_recovery.dart`](../../apps/waddle_display/lib/bootstrap/app_fatal_error_recovery.dart). When framework-internal noise is harmless (e.g. `HardwareKeyboard._assertEventIsRegular` on focus loss / Alt-Tab, layout overflow), add a predicate beside `isRecoverableLayoutFlutterError` / `isRecoverableHardwareKeyboardError` and route it through the recoverable-log path instead of letting it trip a restart. Match on stack-frame library (`package:flutter/src/...`) plus exception type, not on message text — Flutter rewords assertions across releases.
